race.comment: VEYEPEE (10) is a gelding by Russian Camelot on debut for the Anthony & Sam Freedman yard. He won his most recent jump out at Cranbourne and this trip looks a good kick off point for him. The raced form hasn't shown heaps of ability and he can measure right up. CUTTIN' CLASS (6) has raced three times to date, solid in a decent maiden at Cranbourne last start. He can push forward and take beating in this. TERRORTORIAN (4) resumes for his second campaign. His form got a bit better in three runs last time in and he can be an improver this time in, watch the market. TROOPER (5) struggled second up at Cranbourne. The fresh run was okay and he could improve. FIRE TYPE (7) was close up fresh and has each way claims.
